Sorry it has taken so long to respond. My computer crashed and i just got it back up.  Now i see that the site is closing :(  Yes, I think that there needs to be a man from Vietnam interned in the memorial BUT ONLY after all efforts to identify him have been exhausted.  The government recognizes the fact that of the remaining men Missing in Vietnam they feel all but 43 will be identified in time.  Unfortuneately, my dad is on that list that will never be recovered.  To learn more on why, e-mail me and i will gladly share my dedication to my dad with you.<br>
